      <prop type="x-chinese-ref">詩經·小雅·節南山之什·009.8</prop>
      <prop type="x-translation-ref">何人斯.8</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>為鬼為蜮，則不可得。有靦面目，視人罔極。作此好歌，以極反側。</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>If you were an imp or a water-bow,
You could not be got at.
But when one with face and eyes stands opposite to another,
The man can be seen through and through.
I have made this good song,
To probe to the utmost your veerings and turnings.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
